@kushagraThapar found a good bug in Check Enforcer today. He copied and pasted a ```/check-enforcer override``` command from a chat session which included some whitepace at the end of the line. Check Enforcer rejected the command (telemetry):

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/513398/81898720-9d34c580-95fc-11ea-8039-8ef4ec3c6bcb.png)

We should really just truncate the whitespace at the beginning and end of the comment. We've had two instances in the last 7 days (both Kushagra) but I suspect it'll happen from time to time and its a quick fix to reduce frustration and confusion.

